  "prompt": "Is Prime Minister of India a constitutional post?",
  "response": "Yes, the Prime Minister of India is a constitutional post. The position is established by the Constitution of India, which lays out the framework for the political system in the country. The Prime Minister is the head of government and plays a central role in the functioning of the executive branch. The appointment and responsibilities of the Prime Minister are outlined in Articles 74 and 75 of the Indian Constitution. The Prime Minister leads the Council of Ministers and is responsible for aiding and advising the President of India in the exercise of their functions.",
